    "## Q 1. To what does a relative path refer?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "e5ff2b81",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A relative path is a path with respect my current working DIrectory(PWD). "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6a8e1690",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Q 2. Where \\ does an absolute path start with your operating system?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2d53962b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**ANS:-** \n",
    "### In Linux based Operating System it starts with \\.But in windows it starts with c:\n",
    "\n",
    "**For ex:-**  If Absolute Path to a file called assingment.py is **C:\\Users\\Dell\\Pictures\\assingment.py** and my Pwd is **C:\\Users\\Dell**\n",
    "then relate path is Pictures\\assingment.py."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "20b1f670",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. What do the functions os.getcwd() and os.chdir() do?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4d2eaef2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Ans:-**\n",
    "os.getcwd() function tells the current working directory(pwd) whereas os.chdir() is used to \n",
    "       to change the current working directory to a specific path."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "04a15957",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "This is the default working directory :-  C:\\Users\\Dell\\Downloads\n",
      "C:\\Users\\Dell\\Documents\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import os \n",
    "print(\"This is the default working directory :- \",os.getcwd())    # It will print the current working directory.\n",
    "new_path = r'C:\\Users\\Dell\\Documents'\n",
    "os.chdir(new_path)            # it will change the current working directory from default to **new_path**\n",
    "print(os.getcwd())"
   ]
  },
  {
